Mega Energy of New England, LLC FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 1
1) Availability
Mega Energy of New England, LLC %28%22Mega Energy%22%29 makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available under this FERC electric tariff to any purchaser for resale, except as prohibited below.
2) Rates
All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Mega Energy.
3) Seller Category
Mega Energy is a Category 1 seller in all regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. %A7 35.36%28a%29.
4) Compliance with Commission Regulations
Mega Energy shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, subpart H, as applicable, with any conditions the Commission imposes in its order concerning Mega Energy%27s market based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Mega Energy to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Mega Energy%27s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Mega Energy%27s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
5) Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority
Mega Energy does not have any limitations on its market-based rate authority, except as may otherwise be provided in this tariff. Mega Energy has obtained waivers from Subparts B and C of Part 35, regarding the filing of tariffs, except sections 35.12%28a%29, 35.13%28b%29, 35.15, and 35.16; Part 41, regarding accounts, records, and memoranda; Part 101, regarding the uniform system of accounts; and Part 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15, regarding statements and reports. Mega Energy also has blanket approval under Part 34 of the Commission%27s regulations of future issuances regarding securities and assumptions of liabilities, subject to objection by an interested party. See Mega Energy of New England, LLC, Docket No. ER13-_____-000.
6) Ancillary Services
Mega Energy may offer for sale those ancillary services in those markets specified and authorized by the Commission from time to time in orders extending such authority to all sellers authorized to sell electric energy and capacity at market-based rates, including:
a. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service %28which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves%29 for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. %28%22PJM%22%29 and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
b. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service %28which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves%29 for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.
c. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service %28automatic generator control%29, operating reserve service %28which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service%29 to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc.
d. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation %28%22CAISO%22%29 and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO.
e. MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service %28which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve%29 for sale to the Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator, Inc. %28MISO%29 and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO.
f. Third Party Provider: Third-party ancillary services may include Regulation Service, Energy Imbalance Service, Spinning Reserves, and Supplemental Reserves. Sales will not include the following: %281%29 sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; %282%29 sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier; and %283%29 sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers.
7) Effective Date
This tariff is effective on the date specified by the Commission.
